title: Static Time Field
description: Automatically generates `time.data` file on the first page visit, so that updating page files will not change the publication time.
...

~~~ .php
Hook::set('shield.before', function() use($site) {
    if ($page = Lot::get('page')) {
        $time = Path::F($page->path) . DS . 'time.data';
        if ($site->is !== '404' && !File::exist($time)) {
            File::write($page->time)->saveTo($time);
        }
    }
});
~~~

The default [shield][link:../reference/file/shield] uses `$page->update` to show the current date which will outputs the file modification time as the page date. To show the current page date created by this snippet, you can use `$page->time` or `$page->date->{$format}`. Example:

~~~ .php
<p><?php echo $page->date->en_us; ?></p>
~~~

